Thanks @tallinn1960, for requesting the log output.

This was enabled. I tried turn off/on many times. But! Today it suddenly started working! I opened an other project and JxBrowser downloaded. The issue: My project is a multi-library project. The opened root folder contains more than one application and not have pubspec.yaml in the project root. The plugin doesn't recognise the project as a Flutter project and Flutter related tool windows not showing. This is worked before the plugin update. Now the JxBrowser is exists, but tool windows still not showing when I open my multi-lib project. This is the real issue

I created a mock pubspec.yaml in root folder, now it's working. I think there is a new "feature" that hides Flutter tools when the project is not a Flutter project. Would be a nice feature indeed, but not detects Flutter project properly. The solution is a recursive pubspec.yaml search.

I added subfolders as module in project settings. That way working too without pubspec. May can it be an IntelliJ issue that not creates module from source (or not detects Flutter project in subdirectories) when opened first time?
The Flutter plugin does not work with monorepo projects. See #5291
